### Dataset Structure Validation

Repeated column groups were investigated to determine whether they represented duplicated information.

Findings:

* Title columns (A and U) contained matching values in reviewed records.
* Brand columns (B and V) contained matching values in reviewed records.
* MPN columns (C and W) showed differences requiring additional investigation.
* UPC columns (D and X) showed differences requiring additional investigation.

At this stage, no repeated columns have been removed from the dataset.

Further validation is required to determine whether the observed differences represent data quality issues, alternate identifiers, or dataset design choices.


